    ns1:inpersonHours "44 horas (42.3%)"@es ;
    ns1:numberOfCredits 4.0 ;
    ns1:otherInformation ""@es ;
    ns1:periodEndingMonth "Enero"@es ;
    ns1:periodStartingMonth "Septiembre"@es ;
    ns1:teachingPeriod "2025-26" ;
    ns1:teachingPeriodMonths "Septiembre-Enero"@es ;
    ns1:totalHours "60 horas"@es ;
    schema:activitiesWorkload "100%"@es ;
    schema:courseSchedule <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/63000273/2025-26/eventSchedule> ;
    schema:description "The course begins with an analysis of the origin of natural stresses in rock masses, laying the groundwork for understanding their behavior. This is followed by the study of slope stability, focusing on the principles for calculating safety factors and designing support systems. The open-pit mining section concludes with an overview of slope monitoring techniques and instrumentation. The second part of the course focuses on Rock Mechanics applied to underground mining and excavation. Topics include stress distribution around circular and elliptical openings under elastic conditions and methods for assessing stresses in mine pillars. The course also covers procedures for determining the safety factor of tunnel support systems. Other topics include the stability of underground chamber roofs and the design of support pillars. The course addresses the excavation of tunnels using mechanical methods, with a focus on estimating the advance rates of road headers and tunnel boring machines (TBMs). Additionally, the influence of rock mechanical properties on excavation rates and cutter wear is examined. The final part of the course is dedicated to rock mechanics laboratory testing."@es ;
    schema:director <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/santiago.gomez%40upm.es> ;
    schema:inLanguage "Inglés/Castellano"@es ;
    schema:instructor <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/santiago.gomez%40upm.es> ;
    schema:name "Advanced Rock Engineering"@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/63000273/2025-26/CG1> a ns1:Competency ;
