<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/63000273/2025-26/evaluation> a ns1:EvaluationSystem ;
    ns1:evaluationDescription """The grade of Advanced Rock Engineering will be composed of 40% corresponding to the grade obtained in the theoretical part (20 % T1 + 20 % T2), which will consist of multiple-choice tests, and 60% corresponding to the grade obtained in the practical assessments (8 x 7.5 %). To qualify for approval, the following requirements must be met:

An average grade of 5 or higher.
A minimum of 4 points out of 10 in each individual theoretical test.
A minimum of 4 points out of 10 in each individual practical assessment.
The final exam will serve to ensure that, in case the average grade of the progressive assessment tests does not exceed 5 out of 10, the student has an additional opportunity to meet the required standard for approval."""@es .

